JOHANNESBURG (miningweekly.com) &ndash; TSX-listed MacDonald Mines will buy Sage Gold&rsquo;s interest in the Soocana claims, which are adjacent to its Holdsworth property, in the Esquega and Corbiere townships of Northern Ontario. MacDonald will issue four-million units of its class A common shares and warrants to Sage, which will also hold a 1% net smelter return royalty on the property. &quot;We have secured the remainder of the 99-year lease on the Soocana claims. Work done on the claims in the 1930s and 1940s uncovered several quartz veins with varying concentrations of gold,&rdquo; MacDonald CEO Quentin Yarie said in a statement on Tuesday. The Soocana claims comprise a contiguous block of 12 claims that cover 437.3 acres.